details:
 General Dynamics Information Technology (GDIT), a leading provider of systems engineering, integration, IT service operations andsupport solutions, is seeking talented professionals to deliver valuable services and solutions to our customers.GDIT has a great team consisting of experienced and knowledgeable managers who lead and support the career development objectives of our employees. Our employees consider the company to be a solid partner in their career, with an abundance of opportunities for advancement.We are seeking a Sr. Database Administrator to support our Justice Programs team in Washington, DC. In this position, you will support the FBI’s Insider Threat CenterPersonnel supporting this task: 
Evaluate and recommends available database management system products to support validated user requirements; 
Define file organization, indexing methods, and security procedures for specific user applications; 
Maintain Oracle systems on a Linux operating system environment and MS SQL databases on day-to-day basis; 
Responsible for backup and recovery operations for servers; 
Perform quality control of ingest and transform processes and products produced; 
Perform rudimentary Linux systems administrative functions; 
Responsible for entity relational diagrams and documentation of Oracle configuration. 


At least ten (10+) years’ prior experience of information technology. 
(Preferred) Four-year (4-year) degree in applicable discipline. 
Four years (4+) of Oracle database administration experience; 
Three (3+) years of Linux administration experience 
Multiple Information Technology certifications; 
Knowledge of Government-wide system design, information technology equipment and services; and 
Extensive knowledge of methodology, federal information system policies (e.g. NIST 800.53, FISMA, Security Technical Implementation Guide (STIG), configuration management) and knowledge of the FBI’s mission and processes. 
As a trusted systems integrator for more than 50 years, General Dynamics Information Technology provides information technology (IT), systems engineering, professional services and simulation and training to customers in the defense, federal civilian government, health, homeland security, intelligence, state and local government and commercial sectors.With approximately 32,000 professionals worldwide, the company delivers IT enterprise solutions, manages large-scale, mission-critical IT programs and provides mission support services.GDIT is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, or veteran status, or any other protected class.#DICEWIDB50

Position: Database Administrator

Job Purpose: Support Na Ali‘i's client by providing Database and Application Developer Support.

Job Duties: The following reflects management’s definition of essential functions for this job but does not restrict the tasks that may be assigned.  Management may assign additional duties and responsibilities to this job at any time due to reasonable accommodation or other reasons.



 Serve as SQL Database Administrator (DBA).

 Responsible for:

 Database administration;

 Technical oversight of application programmers;

 Web administrator’s systems analysis;

 Application programming;

 Development.



 Modify, enhance, and maintain multiple custom databases used in critical operational missions utilizing:

 PL/SQL;

 Oracle 11g, 12c

 Delphi;

 TOAD;

 Crystal Reports;

 RoboHelp.



 Provide, update, create, and maintain database and document application.

 Enhance, modify, and maintain installation integration and end user training and support for designed systems.

 Provide code quality and peer review analysis for developed systems.

 Support weekly and monthly reporting requirements on all development and maintenance efforts.

 Manage new requirements and developmental priorities with user representative and product owners.


 

Skills/Qualifications: Independently capable of executing analytical methods and data manipulation. Strong technical communication and problem-solving skills, adaptable and customer service oriented. Confident with quantitative analytical methods and technologies, including exposure to relational databases. Experience with data manipulation and data visualization using Microsoft SQL Server and ability to write complex SQL queries. 

Education/Experience: This position requires a bachelor’s degree from an accredited institution as well as a minimum of (8) eight years of relevant professional experience.  IAT II (CCNA Security, CSA+, GICSP, GSEC, Security+ CE, SSCP) and the ability to obtain an OS certification are minimum requirements for this position.

Clearance: This position requires an active TS/SCI level of security clearance.


 Na Ali`i Is Proud to Be an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer
